Doesn't seem to be
a shadow in the city

5
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:41,877
All around
people looking half-dead

6
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,117
Walkin'on the sidewalk
hotter than a match head

7
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:47,390
But at night
it's a different world

8
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:50,910
Go out and find a girl
Come on, come on and dance all night

9
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,837
Despite the heat
it'll be all right

10
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:54,916
And, babe
don't you know it's a pity

11
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:56,996
The days can't be like the nights

12
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:58,917
In the summer in the city

13
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:01,349
In the summer in the city

14
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,277
Cool town
Evening in the city

15
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,470
Dressed so fine
and looking so pretty

16
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,431
Cool cat
Looking for a kitty

17
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:09,630
Gonna look in every corner
of the city

18
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:12,115
Till I'm wheezing
like a bus stop, runnin'--

19
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:30,756
Allen, Bomb Squad,
Special Services...

20
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:33,314
State Police and the FBI!

21
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:37,069
Lieutenant Jurgenson, Upummer! I want
you to go to St.John's Emergency...

22
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:39,555
in case we got any walk-ins
from the street.

23
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:42,114
- Take that down there and get it faxed.
- Kramer, get the city engineer!

24
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:44,470
I gotta find out a damage report.
It's very important.

25
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:47,034
Bonwit Teller. Who the hell would want
to blow up a department store?

26
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,991
Did you ever see a woman
miss a shoe sale?

27
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:51,395
Connie, I want you to get started
on the witness sheet.

28
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:54,751
Ricky, you and Joe, you make sure
the uniforms got it cordoned off there.

29
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:58,190
And you don't let
the damn TV crews in. Benson!

30
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:01,471
- Inspector, phone.
- Not now. Benson! Traffic!

31
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,831
We get Fifth Avenue cleared up by 3:00,
or we got the traffic jam from hell!

32
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,757
- Walter!
- Yeah?

33
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:10,111
I think you'd better take this.

34
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,116
Major Case Unit,
Inspector Cobb.

35
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:16,231
Said Simple Simon to the pie man
going to the fair...

36
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:18,430
''Give me your pies...

37
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:21,313
or I'll cave your head in. ''

38
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:24,671
You see, Bonwit's was just
to make sure I had your attention.

39
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,917
Is there a detective
named McClane there?

40
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:32,716
- He's on suspension.
- No, Walter, he's not. Not today.

41
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:35,479
- Who is this?
- Call me Simon.

42
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:38,558
- What do you want?
- I want to play a game.

43
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:41,478
- What kind of game?
- ''Simon says. ''

44
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:45,309
Simon's going to tell
Lt McClane what to do...

45
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:48,591
and Lt McClane is going to do it.

46
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:51,871
Noncompliance will result
in a penalty.

47
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,797
What penalty?

48
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:57,037
Another big bang
in a very public place.

49
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:02,233
What is it that you want
Lt McClane to do?

50
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,669
Simon says Lt McClane
is to go to the corner...

51
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,439
of 138th Street und Amsterdam...

52
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,630
which is in Harlem
if I'm not mistaken.

53
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:13,639
Kowalski! Lambert!
Do you know where to find McClane?

54
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,796
Well, I kinda doubt
you're gonna find him in church.

55
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:19,196
Well, you better find out
what rock he's under...

56
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:20,719
and kick it over.

57
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:35,835
-John.
- Thanks.

58
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,796
Gimme some more. Come on.

59
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:49,192
Jesus,John.
You look like shit.

60
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:55,829
Where did we leave off
with that roster?

61
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:59,475
We got three killings in Red Hook
the past two nights.

62
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,716
Put Miner on it.
And Genetti.

63
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,717
The mayor's office will call
before the day's out.

64
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:08,152
Next, 14 dump trucks stolen
from a yard in Staten Island.

65
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:12,512
Fourteen!Jesus! Is somebody
starting a construction company?

66
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:15,074
Nah, it was John's landlady
going to clean his apartment.

67
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,356
Insurance fraud.

68
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:22,233
That's a priority
out in California.

69
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:24,316
The contractor splits the money
with the thieves.

70
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,908
We had that out in Jersey
a couple years ago,Joe. Remember?

71
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:30,271
- See what Kelly can do with it.
- Oh, wow.

72
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,356
Hey, what was the lottery number
last night?

73
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,550
- 4667.
- 4667.

74
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:38,197
You still bettin' your badge, Rick?

75
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,993
Yeah, 6991every week.

76
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,996
6991, lucky number.

77
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:47,839
Half the cops in New York
play their badges.

78
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:50,872
How're the kids,John?

79
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,639
I hear they're okay.

80
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:56,035
Did you talk with Holly?

81
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:01,871
- No, I didn't talk to Holly.
- Coming up on it, Inspector.

82
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:05,716
Is it hot in here,
or am I just scared to death?

83
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:09,116
You wanna make sure
the gun's secure?

84
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:11,231
Yeah, it's good.

85
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,794
You know, you're the first woman
since Holly who's seen me do this.

86
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:25,152
- I'm honoured.
- Yeah, so was she.

87
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:31,391
So, where's the backup gonna be?

88
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,438
We're gonna drop back
to 128th Street.

89
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,869
What?

90
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,753
Ten blocks?
Are you fucking kidding me?

91
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:46,270
Oh, man, that's just great! Hey, Walter,
what is all this about, huh?

92
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:49,597
- If we don't do it, this guy says he's
gonna blow up another public place.
- Well, why me?

93
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:53,998
- What does it got to do with me?
- I have no idea. He just said
it had to be you.

94
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,793
It's nice to be needed.

95
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:02,196
- Frankly,John, you haven't been--
- Hey, Walter, how 'bout you mind your
fucking business about Holly, huh?

96
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:06,989
Between you and Simon, you're
fucking up a perfectly good hangover.

97
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:11,757
Okay.

98
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,273
We'll be back to pick you up
in 15 minutes.

99
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:26,551
Take your time.
I expect to be dead in four.

100
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,874
Let's go, Billy!

101
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,197
Oh, man.

102
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,838
- Hey, yo, Uncle.
- Come look at this.

103
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,516
It's ten after 9:00.
Why aren't you in school?

104
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:29,077
- Tony wants to sell you this.
- Tony? That no-neck dude
they call Bad T?

105
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,156
He says he found it
in a Dumpster.

106
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:33,635
He keeps stealing from people,
they're gonna find him in a Dumpster.

107
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:36,638
No, he didn't steal it.
He says his uncle gave it to him.

108
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:39,718
Mm-hmm. Hand me
that newspaper over there.

109
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:44,191
Don't ever let people use you.

110
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:46,117
You're runnin' all over town
with stolen property.

111
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,037
If you get caught,
you get in trouble...

112
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:50,390
while he gets to deny
the whole thing and walk away.

113
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:53,637
You-- You mean you want us
to take it back to Tony?

114
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:56,991
No, I'll take it back to Tony,
with a message.

115
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:00,469
- Now, where you goin'?
- School.

116
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,397
- Why?
- To get educated?

117
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:04,317
- Why?
- So we can go to college.

118
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,590
- And why is that important?
- To get ''espect.''

119
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,597
''Respect.''
And who's the bad guys?

120
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:11,314
- Guys who sell drugs.
- Guys who have guns.

121
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,237
- And who's the good guys?
- We're the good guys.

122
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,237
- Who's gonna help you?
- Nobody.

123
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:17,590
- So who's gonna help you?
- We're gonna help ourselves.

124
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,075
- And who do we not want to help us?
- White people.
- White people.

125
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,714
That's right.

126
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:26,116
Now, get on outta here.
Go to school.

127
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:32,035
- Uncle, you better come look at this.
- What?

128
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,116
There's a white man
standing in the street.

129
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:36,913
- I seen one.
- Not like this.

130
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,880
Dial 9-1-1. Tell the police
to get up here quick.

131
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:53,630
Somebody's about to get killed. And get
your butts to school. You hear me?

132
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:55,910
- Yeah.
- Yeah.
- All right.

133
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:02,718
- I paid 500 bucks--
- You better back off, man.

134
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,913
- Hey, man!
- He ain't so big.

135
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:23,790
- Morning.
- Good morning.

136
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:27,230
You having a nice day, sir?
You feeling all right?

137
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,191
Not to get too personal...

138
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,151
but a white man standin'
in the middle of Harlem...

139
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:33,589
wearin' a sign that says
''I hate niggers''...

140
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,790
has either got some serious
personal issues...

141
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:38,354
or not all his dogs are barkin'.

142
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,948
Hey, I'm talkin' to you!

143
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,674
Now, you got about ten seconds
before those guys see you.

144
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,598
When they do, they will kill you.
You understand?

145
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:50,349
You are about to have
a very bad day.

146
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,995
Tell me about it.
Sir, this is a police matter.

147
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,634
- For your own safety, I'm gonna
ask you to step across the street.
- You damn right it's a police matter!

148
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:59,558
For your own safety, I suggest
you hide your butt in my shop
till the police get here.

149
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:01,716
What the fuck?

150
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:05,840
Aw, shit.

151
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,997
- Listen, I'm a cop. I'm on a case.
- What?

152
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,315
Somebody blew up
Bonwit Teller's an hour ago.
Did you hear about that on the news?

153
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,237
- Yeah.
- The same asshole that did that said...

154
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,157
I gotta come to Harlem and do this
or he's gonna blow up something else.

155
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:22,077
- Do you understand?
- Shit, shit, shit.

156
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,997
- Listen, I got a gun.
You should get across the street.
- They got ten guns.

157
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,917
- You should get across the street!
- Look, start acting crazy, all right?

158
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:28,395
- What?
- Like Looney Tunes.
You know, like Bellevue?

159
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:32,832
- Hey, Zeus, this a friend of yours?
- He look like a friend of mine?

160
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:36,839
I think the dude just escaped from
some hospital. You know, like Bellevue?

161
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:44,919
I am the voice of my own god.

162
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:47,076
And my god did--

163
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,316
I told the librarian that I had a bad
headache, but she didn't believe me.

164
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,193
I really do have a bad headache, though.
I have a very bad headache!

165
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:55,676
- And my head does not feel--
- Oh, man, shut the fuck--

166
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,711
- Who in the fuck--
- You've made a very bad mistake.
- Kick his ass.

167
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,513
- Put it through his head.
- Bust his head.

168
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:04,189
Cut this shit off!
Fellas! Fellas!

169
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:07,551
Nature boy here hates niggers.
Now, what are we gonna do about that?

170
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:10,274
- Fight him!
- Yo, yo, yo, yo!
Hold up! Hold up! Hold up!

171
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:13,119
- Oh, shit!
- Yeah!

172
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:15,356
Get him! Get him!

173
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,313
- Back! Back up!
- Hey, what you trippin' on?

174
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:21,671
- Back the fuck up! Now!
- Hey, you better quit that, boy!

175
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:25,270
Come on, man, get up.
Get up! Get outta here!

176
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,676
Stop the c--
Stop the goddam cab!

177
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,995
- Don't shoot!
No, don't shoot me! Don't shoot!
- Don't move that cab! Get up!

178
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,951
- Come on, get up!
- Yo, you sayin' you gonna kill us?

179
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:36,675
I mean it! I don't want to, but I will!
You know I will! Come on. Drive! Drive!

180
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:39,360
- Drive! Go! Go! Go! Drive, goddam it!
- Oh! Get the fuck outta here!

181
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:42,597
Drive! Drive!
Don't stop! Don't stop!

182
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:45,029
-Just keep driving!
Run the red light! Drive!
- Don't shoot me, man! That's all I got!

183
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:46,957
- That's all I got.
- Man, put that fuckin' money away!

184
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,877
- Nobody's robbing you, asshole!
- Don't kill me!
- Nobody's gonna kill you!

185
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,797
- Shit!
-Just run all the lights! Drive!

186
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,831
- Oh, man! Damn!
- We got a bus.

187
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,757
- That cut deep?
- How the hell would I know?

188
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,996
Just keep pressure on it.

189
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:59,395
Oh, fuck!

190
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:02,990
-Jesus, right? John McClane.
I owe you one.
- Damn right, you owe me!

191
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:05,953
- You got any idea what those guys
are doin' to my shop right now?
- Chill out,Jesus!

192
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,877
- We'll send a car for--
- ''Chill out''? What the fuck?
Are you tryin' to relate to me?

193
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,195
- Talk like a white man!
- Okay.Jesus, I'm sorry
you got involved, all right?

194
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:12,356
Why do you keep calling me Jesus?
I look Puerto Rican to you?

195
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:14,710
- Guy back there
called you Jesus, didn't he?
- He didn't say Jesus!

196
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:17,832
- He said, ''Hey, Zeus.'' My name is Zeus.
- Zeus?

197
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,838
Yeah, Zeus! As in father of Apollo!
Mount Olympus!

198
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:23,713
''Don't fuck with me, or I'll shove
a lightning bolt up your ass!''

199
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:26,832
Zeus! You got a problem with that?

200
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:29,474
- No, I don't have a problem with that.
- Shit!

201
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:33,309
- Downtown. Police Plaza.
- Oh-ho! That's just great.

202
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:39,998
Get a record of all his collars,
recent releases...

203
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:42,076
and a list of anybody else
he might have looked at sideways.

204
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,395
It's probably as long as your arm,
so I'm gonna need some help with it.

205
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:47,353
It's textbook megalomania.
It's a pathological state...

206
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:50,631
in which fantasies of control
or omnipotence predominate.

207
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:54,230
He wants control over him.
He wants control over his actions,
over his thoughts, even his emotions.

208
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:57,955
-Sounds like you got
a secret admirer,John.
-Yeah, maybe he'll send me some flowers.

209
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:01,311
- Everybody knows you like pansies.
- It's not that kind of emotion.

210
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,635
- This guy is ugly.
- How is that?

211
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:06,433
Nothin' wrong with him
a shower wouldn't cure.

212
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,994
Beer is normally taken
internally,John.

213
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:12,192
-Just get me some aspirins, will ya?
- Yeah, okay. Hold this here.

214
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,157
This is Fred Schiller,John,
and he's a--

215
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:18,829
-A shrink. Yeah, I got it.
-Yes. I was saying that we're dealing...

216
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:21,918
with a megalomaniacal personality
with possible paranoid schizophrenia.

217
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:26,079
Hey, hey, how about we just skip down
to the part where you tell me what
the fuck this has to do with me, huh?

218
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:30,034
I don't know. I mean,
what I do know is it does have
specifically to do with you.

219
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:33,391
This guy wants to pound on you
till you crumble.

220
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,317
He wants you to dance
to his tune and then--

221
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:38,352
Put on a dress and fuck me?

222
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:40,516
I was going to say kill you.

223
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:43,393
-Pick up five, goddam it!
-He's sitting on an awful lot of rage...

224
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:46,796
and it could be manifested physically
if he's stressed.

225
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:49,070
Somebody he arrested?
Somebody he pissed off?

226
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,873
- That could be one hell of a long list.
- Fuck you,Joe.

227
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,150
See, these people don't like
to work anonymously.

228
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,555
They want you to know
who's doing it to you.

229
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,477
So this name ''Simon''
is probably not an alias.

230
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,875
It's probably ''Simon''
or some variation.

231
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:04,879
''Simon, Robert E. Busted in '86,
extortion, kidnapping, ten to fifteen.

232
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:08,390
Did seven years for good behaviour.
Released on a state work-furlough
two months ago.''

233
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:10,351
- Check it.
- Thanks, Rick.

234
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:13,756
Bob Simons was a bankrupt businessman
who kidnapped his partner's daughter.

235
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:16,633
He's a fuckup, not a psycho.
The guy we're lookin' for is nuts.

236
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:19,513
A nut who knows a lot about bombs.

237
00:14:19,640 --> 00:14:22,279
We found this in a playground.
Professional!

238
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:25,358
Very cool stuff.
You know, boom!

239
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:29,234
- You think you should
slam it around like that, Charlie?
- When it's unmixed, you can't hurt it.

240
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,828
This stuff is cutting edge.
It's a binary liquid.

241
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,713
- A what?
- Like epoxy.

242
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,671
Two liquids.

243
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:39,314
Either one by itself...

244
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:43,871
you got nothin', but mix 'em--

245
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:56,397
Ricky.

246
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,868
Charlie, you're gonna be wearing
that shirt up your ass!

247
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:06,151
- Christ Almighty, Charlie!
- Like I said, very cool stuff.

248
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,589
Now, with a package like this,
you get a warning.

249
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:10,676
Now, the bomb has to arm itself.

250
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:14,952
You'll see the red liquid
pump into the clear before it detonates.

251
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:18,231
- How long before?
- Ten seconds, two minutes.

252
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:20,157
Could be anything.

253
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:23,511
But once it's mixed,
be somewhere else.

254
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:25,437
This stuff has gotta be pretty rare.

255
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:27,391
We oughta be able to find out
if any of it's missin' somewhere.

256
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:30,478
I already did. Livermore Labs
theft over the weekend.

257
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,716
He got enough to make
another one,Joe?

258
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:35,877
- About 2,000 pounds.
- Of that?

259
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:39,231
Well, the detonating mechanism
could be anything-- radio, electrical.

260
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,669
Hell, you could use a beeper
and phone it in.

261
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:45,839
- Inspector? Inspector, it's him.
- He's got a double Alberti
feedback loop on it.

262
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:48,713
- A nasty little trick
I believe once used in Lebanon.
- Charlie. Charlie!

263
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,398
- Charlie, shh!
- What?

264
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:52,317
Wanna start the trace?

265
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,599
Simon.

266
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:03,632
He wore the board,
walked the street and survived.

267
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:08,834
- Where are my pigeons now?
- Pigeons?

268
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:12,396
I had two pigeons, bright and gay,
fly from me the other day.

269
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:15,751
Why was it they did go?
You cannot tell. You do not know.

270
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:19,555
- You mean McClane?
- No, I mean Santa Claus.

271
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:26,158
- Yeah, I'm here.
- Ah, there after all. And your friend?

272
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:28,748
Carver! Carver! Come on.
We need you in the other room.

273
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:32,077
- Let's go! Come on!
- They need you. Go.

274
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:34,953
- Yeah, he's here too.
- And may I speak with him?

275
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:39,116
Well, is the ebony
Samaritan there now?

276
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:41,674
- You got a problem with ebony?
- No, no.

277
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:45,873
My only problem is that I went to some
trouble preparing that game for McClane.

278
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,150
You interfered
with a well-laid plan.

279
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:52,239
Yeah? Well, you can stick your
well-laid plan up your well-laid ass.

280
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:58,433
That was not smart.
There are lives at stake here!

281
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:01,950
- Not enough time, Inspector.
- You better hope he calls back.

282
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,513
He will.

283
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,558
Ricky, you wanna tell those people
to shut the hell up out there!

284
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:11,478
Hey, keep it down here!

285
00:17:19,280 --> 00:17:22,556
Simon, he wasn't speaking
for all of us.

286
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:25,831
That was unpleasant.
Don't let it happen again.

287
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:29,032
- So, what's your name, boy?
- Don't call me ''boy.''

288
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:32,357
I'm sorry.
It was a poor attempt at humour.

289
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:34,596
I was going to send you home
with a chiding...

290
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,359
- but now I think perhaps
you should join the game.
- We got him!

291
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,436
It's a pay phone in Oslo.

292
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,357
- No, w-wait, they say
it's Juarez, Mexico.
- Norway?

293
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:44,040
No, wait. No, wait. N-Now
they're saying it's Juarez, Mexico.

294
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:47,596
Forget it! Australia?
He's scrambling up their system.
They don't know where he is.

295
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:50,553
Having fun with
the phone company, are we?

296
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:53,353
Simon says,
McClane and the Samaritan...

297
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:56,233
will go to the subway station
at 72nd and Broadway.

298
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:59,511
I will call you in 15 minutes
on the pay phone outside the station.

299
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:03,189
No police. Failure to answer
will constitute noncompliance.

300
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:05,675
Do you understand me,John?

301
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:08,872
Oh, yes, I understand. I understand
that you're a fuckin' wacko...

302
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,036
that likes to play kids games,
that's what I understand.

303
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,957
- Hardly.
- Hardly?

304
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:16,231
Well, then, who are you?
Somebody I sent up? What'd you do?

305
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:20,399
Shoplifting? Purse snatching?
Cross dressing? What?

306
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:24,638
You c-c-couldn't catch me if I stole
your ch-chair with you in it.

307
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:28,469
My ch-ch-ch-chair with me in it?
Ooh-hoo! That's very exciting.

308
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:32,354
Let me ask you a question, bonehead.
Why are you trying to k-k-k-kill me?

309
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:35,438
- John,John, calm yourself.
- Huh? Why don't you come on
down here to Police Plaza...

310
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,391
and we'll figure this out
like a couple of men, huh?

311
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:40,432
-Just come on down here.
- If killing you was all I wanted...

312
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:42,949
- Simon, this is Inspector Cobb.
- you'd be dead by now.

313
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:45,640
I can appreciate your feelings
for McClane...

314
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:48,320
but believe me,
the jerk isn't worth it.

315
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:50,635
He's stepped on so many toes
in this department...

316
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:53,194
by this time next month
he's gonna be a security guard.

317
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:55,356
His own wife wants
nothing to do with him...

318
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:58,472
and he's about two steps shy
of becoming a full-blown alcoholic.

319
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:01,034
One step. One step.

320
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,991
Now listen to me.

321
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:06,715
You sound like a real smart guy.
What is it that you want?

322
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:08,831
Are you talking about money?

323
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:11,599
Well, whatever, whatever.

324
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:14,234
McClane is a toilet bug.

325
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:17,670
Now what would it take just to forget
him and live happily ever after?

326
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,631
You know, money is shit to me.

327
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:23,833
I would not give up McClane
for all the gold in your Fort Knox.

328
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:26,952
72nd Street subway,
pay phone, 15 minutes.

329
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:28,957
McClane and the Samaritan.

330
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:31,594
If you're competent in the least,
you've found the briefcase...

331
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:34,518
so you know what I mean by penalty.

332
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:39,390
I wanna thank you for that vote
of confidence, Walter.

333
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:42,398
Well, I thought it was worth a try.
This guy's a raving maniac.

334
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:45,034
Well, he-he couldn't be any clearer
if he got it from a case history.

335
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,071
He gave you clues
to his identity.

336
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,998
He spoke German.
He called it ''your Fort Knox.''

337
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,838
And he stammered
when McClane pushed him.

338
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,996
Now, you believe this guy
really can't be bought?

339
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:58,159
There's no chance. The very mention
of money only enraged him further.

340
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:09,110
- What's that?
- It's your shield.

341
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:11,595
- You askin' me to be
a cop again, Walter?
- Ricky, get him his gun, all right?

342
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:15,429
- You didn't answer my question. Hey!
-Joe, this time they--

343
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:19,951
- You didn't answer my question, Walter.
- Are you done, Lieutenant?

344
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:24,551
Now, you two better get going if you're
going to get up to 72nd Street on time.

345
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,148
-Joe, this time they go with backup.
- You got it.

346
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:29,840
- Come on, you guys!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
I'm not goin' anywhere.

347
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:33,999
- Simon says you gotta go!
- I'm not jumpin' through hoops
for some psycho!

348
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:36,634
That's a white man with white problems.
You deal with him.

349
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:41,515
- Call me when he crosses 110th Street.
- Hey! Why'd you save my ass?

350
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:45,474
I didn't. I stopped a white cop
from gettin' killed in Harlem.

351
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,477
One white cop gets killed today...

352
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:51,036
tomorrow we got a thousand white cops,
all of 'em with itchy trigger fingers.

353
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:55,392
- Got it?
- Get him back.

354
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:59,796
- Charlie, where'd you find that bomb?
- Chinatown.

355
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:01,831
Shit.

356
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:04,758
Zeus! Yo, partner! Wait up!

357
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,677
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
I ain't your partner.

358
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:10,315
I ain't your neighbour, your brother
or your friend. I'm your total stranger.

359
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,595
Okay, stranger...

360
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:16,871
you know where that park is
at 115th Street and St Nicholas?

361
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:22,789
- Yeah, it's in Harlem.
- Where do you think
we found that bomb?

362
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:28,074
Listen, this guy doesn't care
about skin colour, even if you do.

363
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:33,869
- What am I doin'?
- Cheer up. Things could be worse.

364
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,150
I was workin'
on a nice, fat suspension...

365
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:38,236
smokin' cigarettes
and watchin' Captain Kangaroo.

366
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,559
Come on.

367
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,477
Is that the phone?

368
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,150
Okay, they made it to the phone,
but there's a problem.

369
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:53,191
Well, what do you mean?
How big a problem?

370
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:55,231
Oh, about 300 pounds.

371
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:57,351
- And they're probably going to end up
having to get an operation.
- Ma'am? Excuse me, ma'am.

372
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:59,277
- We need this phone
for official police business.
- Do you mind!

373
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,197
- Honey, I'm a cop.
I need the phone right now.
- I'm sorry, but I can no--

374
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,629
Get off the damn phone, lady!
Police business!

375
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:06,035
- Well, I never!
- I can get used to this.

376
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:08,720
I'm sure you can find a phone
across the street, ma'am.

377
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:11,434
Let's get something straight.
I'm the only one here
on official police business.

378
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:14,120
- Don't ever do that shit again.
- Let's get somethin' else straight.

379
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,390
You need me
a lot more than I need you.

380
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:19,398
You don't like the way
I do things, fine. I quit.

381
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:24,317
I don't know.

382
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:30,155
All right, I need you.

383
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:38,471
All right, I need you
more than you need me.

384
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:45,676
- Hello!
- Birds of a feather flock together.
So do pigs and swine.

385
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,712
Rats and mice have their chance,
as will I have mine.

386
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:50,671
Nice. Rhymes.

387
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:54,315
- Why was the phone busy?
Who were you calling?
- The Psychic Hotline.

388
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:56,237
I'd advise you to take this
more seriously.

389
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:58,157
Look, it's a public phone!
What do you want me to say?

390
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:02,239
You can simply say
there was a fat woman on it, and it
took you a minute to get her off.!

391
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:07,076
Now,John, there's a significant
amount of explosive...

392
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:09,031
in the trash receptacle next to you.

393
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:13,069
Try to run,
and it goes up now.

394
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,270
Nobody's gonna run, but I got
a hundred people out here!

395
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:18,995
That's the point.
Now, do I have your attention?

396
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:21,588
As I was going to St Ives,
I met a man with seven wives.

397
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:24,234
Every wife had seven sacks.
Every sack had seven cats.

398
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:26,794
Every cat had seven kittens.
Kittens, cats, sacks and wives.

399
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:30,117
How many were going to St Ives?
My phone number is 555--

400
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:32,993
- No, no, no! Wait! I didn't
get all that! Say it again!
- Not a chance.

401
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,157
- My phone number is 555 and the answer.
- But I didn't--

402
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:38,475
Call me in 30 seconds or die.

403
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,788
- All right,
seven guys with seven wives makes--
- Shut up, McClane. I'm good at this.

404
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:47,356
- Seven guys with seven wives makes--
- Shut the fuck up, McClane!
He said seven wives with seven sacks.

405
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:49,869
- Seven times seven is 49.
Now tell me the rest.
- Seven wives?

406
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,070
- Uh, a sack with--
s-seven sacks with seven--
- Weren't you listening?

407
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,111
- Yeah, I was listening.
I didn't hear every fuckin' thing--
- What the heck is wrong with you?

408
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:56,913
- Well, I-- Besides having
a bad fuckin' hangover, for one thing!
- All right, all right, all right.

409
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:59,156
Seven wives times seven, 49.
With seven cats.

410
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:01,316
Seven times 49 is 343, right?

411
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:04,716
- What, are you asking me or telling me?
- I'm telling you. 343 times seven is--

412
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:08,753
One, zero, 24. 2,401.
That's what you got, right?

413
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:10,836
Yeah, that's what I got.
Is that it, 2,401?

414
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:14,236
- That's it. Dial. 5 5 5-2401.
- 5 5 5-2401.

415
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:18,478
- No, wait, wait!
It's a trick. It's a trick.
- What? What? What do you mean?

416
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:21,114
- I forgot about the man.
- What man? Fuck the man!
We got ten seconds left!

417
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,310
He said how many were going
to St Ives, right?

418
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:26,796
The riddle begins: As I was going to
St Ives, I met a man with seven wives.

419
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:29,718
- The guy and his wives
aren't goin' anywhere.
- What are they doing?

420
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:32,354
Sittin' in the fuckin' road
waitin' on a mo--
How the hell should I know, McClane?

421
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:35,790
- Well, who's going to St Ives then?
- The guy.Just the guy.

422
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,831
-Just one guy? Just one guy.
- The answer's one.

423
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:40,474
- How do you dial one?
- 5 5 5-0001.

424
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:43,319
- Zero, zero, one.Just one guy's going?
- Hello,John.

425
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:45,715
Yeah, piece of cake.
Give us somethin' harder next time.

426
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:48,400
- But you're ten seconds late.
- No, no! The answer is one! The--

427
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:51,034
- Boom.!
- There's a bomb in the trash! Get down!
- Everybody, get down!

428
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:54,232
Get down! There's a bomb!
Everybody, get down!

429
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:56,715
There's a bomb!

430
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:59,308
Get down! There's a bomb!

431
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,430
- Welcome to New York.
- Really.

432
00:25:06,360 --> 00:25:09,716
They were just talking.
Here, you can have it. Come on.

433
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:12,035
- Come on, let's go.
- I'm getting outta here right now.

434
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:22,592
- I told you it wasn't a bomb.
- I thought there was a bomb!

435
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:27,591
No bomb.

436
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:36,556
- Yeah.
- I didn't say ''Simon says. ''

437
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:41,231
It's 9.:50,John.
The number 3 train is arriving now.

438
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:44,591
I left something provocative
on that train,John.

439
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:46,950
Simon says,
get to the pay phone...

440
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:50,231
next to the news kiosk
in Wall Street Station by 10.:20...

441
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:53,477
- Half an hour.
- or the number 3 train
and its passengers vaporize.

442
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:56,990
Use any means of travel
other than civilian, I blow the train.

443
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:59,588
Attempt to evacuate the subway,
I blow the train.

444
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:02,439
I'll call you in 30 minutes.
Be there.

445
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,958
- We're fucked.
- Ninety blocks in 30 minutes?

446
00:26:06,080 --> 00:26:09,516
In New York traffic?
It could be double that.

447
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:12,234
We don't even have a car!

448
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:14,316
Hey! Hey! Sir! Sir!
I'm a cop! I'm a cop!

449
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:16,874
- I am requisitioning this car
for official police business.
- Hey, what are you doing?

450
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,468
- Thank you very much. Get in! Get in!
- What the fuck you doing to my car?
- Pretty slick.

451
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:22,876
Listen, I used to drive a cab.
The fastest way south is--

452
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:25,434
What the fuck are you doing?

453
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:34,113
- What were you sayin'?
- I was saying I used to drive a cab.

454
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:38,153
Ninth Avenue is the fastest way south.
But we seem to be going east.

455
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:46,998
Where the hell are you going, McClane?
I told you Ninth Avenue
was the quickest way south!

456
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:50,669
- Stop with that goddam yelling!
I know what I'm doing!
- Not even God knows what you're doing!

457
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:53,360
They're headed east on 72nd
towards the park.

458
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:56,597
- But Wall Street is south!
- Man, stop yelling at me!
I got a bad headache!

459
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:59,996
And the best way south is not
Ninth Avenue, it's through the park.

460
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:03,755
Oh, dear.

461
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:05,916
I told you the park drive
is always jammed.

462
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:08,600
I didn't say park drive.

463
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:12,237
I said through the park.

464
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:17,559
Shit! We lost 'em.
They're in the park headed south.

465
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:22,270
- Get outta here!
- Fucking prick!

466
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:30,871
I got him, Connie.
He's taking the scenic route.

467
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:33,355
- Outta the way!
- Oh, man.

468
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:37,836
Get out! Get outta there!

469
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,837
Watch it, watch it, watch it,
watch it! Oh, my God!

470
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:45,757
Are you-- Are you aiming
for these people?

471
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:48,235
No. Well, maybe that mime.

472
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:51,432
Whoa! Tree! Tree! Tree! Oh!

473
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:58,155
- Whoa!
- What's goin' on here?

474
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:02,430
Look out! Whoa!

475
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:06,632
- Tree! Tree!
-Just hang on.

476
00:28:06,760 --> 00:28:09,354
Rock! Rock! Rock!

477
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:12,993
Whoa!

478
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:17,351
Hey, look out down there!

479
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:21,109
McClane! McClane, watch it.

480
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:27,078
McClane!

481
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:34,515
Come on! Outta the way!

482
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:37,108
- How do Catholics do their thing?
- North, south, west, east.

483
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:39,911
- How much time?
- Twenty-seven minutes.

484
00:28:40,040 --> 00:28:43,396
Ha! 72nd and Broadway
to Central Park South in three minutes!

485
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:46,796
That's gotta be a fuckin' record.

486
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,514
Come on, get out--

487
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:52,279
Yeah. Now what?

488
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:00,790
- We need a fire truck.
- What?

489
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,717
To follow.

490
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:08,315
- 9-1-1.
- Lt John McClane, NYPD.

491
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:11,273
Access number 7 4 79.
Calling from a civilian transmitter.

492
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:14,551
- Get me an emergency
dispatcher right away.
- Dispatch. Go ahead.

493
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:17,035
I got two officers down at the corner
of 14th Street and Ninth Avenue!

494
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:19,276
Need an ambulance! Over!

495
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:22,392
Emergency calls on the west side
go to Roosevelt Hospital.
That's two blocks from here.

496
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:51,758
- Slow the fuck down, McClane!
- Kinda like football, isn't it?

497
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:55,031
- What?
- Get yourself a blocker
and head for the end zone!

498
00:29:57,960 --> 00:30:00,235
If you'd said Wall Street,
we could've followed him all the way.

499
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:02,510
Wrong! South of 14th Street's
a different hospital!

500
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:05,473
- Oh.
- St Luke's. Hang on.

501
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:17,358
- Time?
- 10:02.

502
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:19,789
We're halfway there
with 18 minutes to go.

503
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:21,797
Fuck this! Hang on.

504
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:37,750
Hang on. Get outta there!
Slide over and take the wheel.

505
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,950
- Where you goin'?
- We should be ahead
of that train, right?

506
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:43,152
- You're not gonna get on that train--
- I'm gonna get on that train! You gotta
get to that pay phone by 10:20!

507
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:45,077
- What are you gonna do?
- I'm gonna get that bomb.

508
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:47,873
Listen, you fail, I cover your ass.
I fail, you cover my ass.

509
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:51,310
- And if we both fail?
- Then we're both fucked.

510
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:54,910
Go now! Drive! Get to that
phone booth by 10:20! Go!

511
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:57,474
My lucky fuckin' day.

512
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:03,194
Shit! Look out, ma'am!

513
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:09,029
Look out! Look out! Look out!
Get outta the way!

514
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:17,354
This is a bad idea!

515
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:19,752
Oh!

516
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:37,675
Whoa!

517
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,438
- Excuse me! Excuse me!
- Hey!

518
00:31:44,560 --> 00:31:47,518
Just get outta the way, please!

519
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:03,713
- 112 Wall Street.
- Wait. This isn't a taxi.
You don't understand.

520
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:06,070
Your light's on.
I'll make it simple.

521
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:09,397
112 Wall Street, or I'll have
your medallion suspended.

522
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:12,557
What, you don't like
white people?

523
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:17,117
112 Wall Street?
You got it.

524
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:22,677
Come on.

525
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:28,472
Fuck!
Move your legs, sir.

526
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:31,068
Get your legs outta the way!
Sorry. Sorry.

527
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:46,193
- Hey! Excuse me!
- 1823405--

528
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:56,717
Hey!

529
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:13,028
Shit!

530
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:16,390
Excuse me! Watch out!
Excuse me, sir.

531
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:18,590
Pardon me, please. Excu--

532
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:22,717
- Will you step outta here for a minute.
- What?

533
00:33:22,840 --> 00:33:26,071
I'm a cop. Step out of here
for a minute, please. Will ya?

534
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:54,029
Excuse me, please!
Let me get through here, please!

535
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:58,153
- It's him.
- Excuse me. Excuse me, please. Pardon.

536
00:33:58,280 --> 00:34:01,238
Excuse me, sir, but I'm expecting
a call. I need that phone.

537
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:03,920
Why don't you use
the other phone?

538
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:11,276
Sir, please.
I need to use that phone.

539
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:14,039
Hey, listen, bro,
I was here first.

540
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:17,869
''Bro''? Get away
from the goddam phone!

541
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:20,560
Put your hands up!

542
00:34:35,880 --> 00:34:39,634
- I have to answer that phone.
-Just shut up and get 'em in the air!

543
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:43,196
Watch it! Excuse me! Pardon me!
Watch, watch your back! Watch it!

544
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:45,515
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm a New York police officer.

545
00:34:45,640 --> 00:34:49,519
I'm gonna ask you to calmly
and quietly start moving towards
the other end of the car.

546
00:34:49,640 --> 00:34:52,598
Go now, please! Go now!

547
00:34:52,720 --> 00:34:55,632
Fuck! Let's go!
Watch it! Watch out!

548
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:58,320
Watch-- Watch it! Go!

549
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:04,356
I have to answer that phone.

550
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:06,710
Get 'em up!

551
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:09,991
Look, if you have to shoot me...

552
00:35:10,120 --> 00:35:13,032
then you go ahead
and you shoot me!

553
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:17,517
But I have to answer this phone,
all right?

554
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:26,275
- I'm here.
- And McClane?

555
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:29,551
He's on his way. Uh, you know, he's
a little slow. He's kinda out of shape.

556
00:35:29,680 --> 00:35:34,151
The rules applied to both of you.
I'm afraid this is noncompliance.

557
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:36,111
Goodbye.

558
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:46,958
Trust me, guys. Duck.

559
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:24,919
Hey, get outta there!
Get outta there! Duck, asshole!

560
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:49,837
Oh, my God!

561
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:15,799
McClane?

562
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:23,759
What?

563
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:31,436
-You can see right down into the subway.
-How many fire trucks do you count?

564
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:34,358
- You guys! You guys!
- How can you see it from up here?

565
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,877
Damn! Get in there.

566
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:40,709
Officer, tell those people
to get the hell back, will ya?

567
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:43,274
We got a shitload of cuts and bruises,
a couple concussions...

568
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:45,994
some old guy's pacemaker stopped,
and a pregnant girl's water broke.

569
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:48,190
And that's all.
How're you doin',John?

570
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,436
Still can't hear too good.

571
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:53,552
Well, it's a miracle you're still alive.
It's a goddam miracle.

572
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:55,910
- Yeah, that's the problem,Joe.
- What?

573
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:59,715
The miracle part. What are the odds
of us makin' it down here on time?

574
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:03,070
- Zip.
- That bomb was gonna go off
no matter what.

575
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:05,350
He wanted it to go off
right down here.

576
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,869
Take this off me, Dave.

577
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:10,195
Well, what's so special
about this place?

578
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:12,880
- I don't know.
Something just doesn't add up.
- Lt McClane?

579
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:15,594
-Huh?
-They're asking for you and a Mr Carver.

580
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:19,919
- Where?
-John?

581
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:25,793
John, this is Andy Cross
with the FBI.

582
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:29,879
- This is MrJarvis. He's, uh--
- I'm, uh, with another agency.

583
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,673
- It's good to meet you.
- This is Lt McClane.

584
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:35,598
This is Mr Carver.

585
00:38:35,720 --> 00:38:38,280
Uh, we've got
a couple of questions first.

586
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,595
Do you recognize this guy?

587
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:47,877
- No.
- How about this one?

588
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:54,275
- Mm-mm.
- How about you?

589
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,309
Did you recognize
the voice on the phone?

590
00:38:58,440 --> 00:39:00,237
No.

591
00:39:00,360 --> 00:39:02,999
Did you, uh, notice
any cars following you?

592
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:08,708
- No.
- Anybody following you at all?

593
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:11,354
Any kind of surveillance?
Telephone? House?

594
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:14,392
Anything unusual at all?

595
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:18,911
Well, now that you mention it,
I have experienced a--

596
00:39:19,040 --> 00:39:21,429
you know, like a burning sensation
between my toes.

597
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:24,677
I thought it was just some athlete's
foot or something. I don't know.

598
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:31,359
We read your jacket, Lieutenant.
We were told you would be cooperative.

599
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:33,277
- Cooperate with what?
What do you mean cooperate?
- Hey, now wait a minute. He will be.

600
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:35,914
- We're wasting time
here in this goddam van.
- You wanna share information...

601
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:37,837
how about sending
a little our way as well?

602
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:40,110
- Look, we wanna hear
what he knows first.
- What the hell?

603
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:42,800
- You give us pictures, and then you--
- Look, we want to hear
what he knows first.

604
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:45,195
Hey, I know as much as you know.
All right?

605
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,908
There's a guy out there
settin' off bombs.

606
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:52,555
He calls himself Simon.
He speaks with a German accent.

607
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:55,478
And, for some reason,
he's very angry with me.

608
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:58,239
Now, maybe you can tell me
why, fellas. Huh?

609
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:07,114
The first man there is Methias Targo.
Was Hungarian army.

610
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:09,879
Explosives expert. Now we believe
he's working for the Iranians.

611
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:13,834
- Working?
- Freelance terrorism, by contract.

612
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:17,117
- Who's the girl?
- Targo's other half.

613
00:40:17,240 --> 00:40:19,629
Rumour is the Israelis slipped a bomb
in between their sheets.

614
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:23,355
Uh, he wasn't at home,
but they think maybe they got her.

615
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:27,598
The second man was an obscure colonel
in the East German army.

616
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:31,918
He ran an infiltration unit.
The kind of thing the Nazis did
at the Battle of the Bulge.

617
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:34,952
- English-speaking troops--
- Yeah, yeah, I saw the movie.

618
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:40,995
All we know of him is the G.D.R. medical
records show he suffers from migraines.

619
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:43,873
His name is Peter Krieg.

620
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:49,556
Well, that is
an exceptional report, fellas.

621
00:40:49,680 --> 00:40:52,114
Now do you wanna tell me
what the hell this has to do with me?

622
00:40:52,240 --> 00:40:54,800
The name Gruber mean anything
to you, Lieutenant?

623
00:40:59,080 --> 00:41:02,675
- It rings a bell, yeah.
- LA.

624
00:41:02,800 --> 00:41:05,678
- What?
- That thing in the building in LA.

625
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:09,960
Peter Krieg was born...

626
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:13,152
Simon Peter Gruber.

627
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:17,317
He's Hans Gruber's brother.

628
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:25,119
- Oh, shit.
- Yeah, it's that thing in LA.

629
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:28,198
We figure he's got you
fitted up for a toe tag...

630
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:31,153
and he's gonna do anything
to get it tied.

631
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:33,999
Inspector!
Inspector, it's him!

632
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:37,795
Don't let him know we're here.

633
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:43,713
- Simon.
- Inspector.

634
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:46,593
Now, who from the FBI
is in the van, I wonder?

635
00:41:46,720 --> 00:41:48,756
Let's see.
Almost certainly Cross.

636
00:41:48,880 --> 00:41:51,474
- Come on, Andrew. Say hello.
- Hello.

637
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:54,797
And I know you never run alone,
so say hello, Bill.

638
00:41:54,920 --> 00:41:58,037
Still trying to butch up
by chewing on your glasses, huh?

639
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:04,556
This, gentlemen, as they say,
is where the plot thickens.

640
00:42:04,680 --> 00:42:06,750
I have put 2,400 pounds of explosive...

641
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:09,997
in one of the 1,446 schools
in greater New York.

642
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:14,318
It is fitted with a timer
set to explode at exactly 3.:00 pm.

643
00:42:15,720 --> 00:42:18,109
Thank you.
Your silence says I'm understood.

644
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:20,834
Did you say 2,400 pounds?

645
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:22,791
Yes, but please
don't interrupt again.

646
00:42:22,920 --> 00:42:25,514
Simon says, if you attempt
to evacuate schools...

647
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:27,596
the bomb will be detonated
by radio.

648
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:29,790
And, gentlemen,
someone will be watching.

649
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:33,799
Repeat, one school will be dismissed
at 3.:00 pm, permanently.

650
00:42:33,920 --> 00:42:35,558
- Unless--
- Unless what?

651
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:39,389
Unless John McClane and his new best
friend complete the tasks I set them.

652
00:42:39,520 --> 00:42:41,511
John, are you listening?

653
00:42:43,080 --> 00:42:44,513
Yeah.

654
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:47,393
The pay phone beyond Hope,
Tomkins Square Park.

655
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:50,193
Twenty minutes.
Go by foot. No rush.

656
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:54,279
If you're really clever,
you'll learn the location of the bomb
and the code to disarm it.

657
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,277
Oh, and by the way, gentlemen...

658
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:59,278
we got something of a bargain
on radio detonators.

659
00:42:59,400 --> 00:43:01,675
The only problem is
the darn things seem to respond...

660
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:03,791
to police and FBI frequencies.

661
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:07,071
So, if I were you,
I'd keep off your radios.

662
00:43:07,200 --> 00:43:08,997
Simon, wait.

663
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:15,878
Twenty-four hundred pounds
of that liquid stuff.

