01:01:50,480 --> 01:01:52,277
Hey, hey, hey. Where're you going?
Come here. What are you doin'?

887
01:01:52,400 --> 01:01:54,595
- What are you doin'?
- Let me go! Let me go, dick-head.

888
01:01:54,720 --> 01:01:56,119
Watch your mouth.

889
01:01:56,240 --> 01:01:59,357
You wanna go down to juvenile hall
for a Butterfinger? Is that it?

890
01:01:59,480 --> 01:02:02,153
Look around, man.
All the cops are into somethin'.

891
01:02:02,280 --> 01:02:04,236
It's Christmas.
You could steal City Hall.

892
01:02:11,280 --> 01:02:12,998
- Come on. Let's go. Come on.
- My bike.

893
01:02:13,120 --> 01:02:15,350
- Yo, that's my bike!
- Yeah. It's Christmas.

894
01:02:15,480 --> 01:02:19,519
- Hey, hey, hey! Where're you going?
Yankee Stadium's that way!
- That's my bike, you asshole!

895
01:02:25,840 --> 01:02:28,718
Why don't you just run over everybody
in the whole street?

896
01:02:28,840 --> 01:02:31,229
McClane, what the fuck
are we doin' back down here?

897
01:02:31,360 --> 01:02:33,999
Let me ask you somethin'. What is it
that Wall Street doesn't have?

898
01:02:34,120 --> 01:02:35,917
What, is this stuff catchin'?
You're talkin' in riddles.

899
01:02:36,040 --> 01:02:38,474
- No, no. Stay with me. What is it
that Wall Street does not have?
- What?

900
01:02:38,600 --> 01:02:41,672
Schools. And what is it
they have a shitload of?

901
01:02:41,800 --> 01:02:43,756
What?

902
01:02:50,760 --> 01:02:53,991
- I'll be back in a minute.
- What am I supposed to do with this?

903
01:02:55,600 --> 01:02:57,397
Give it to those guys over there.

904
01:02:57,520 --> 01:02:58,669
He's here.

905
01:02:58,800 --> 01:03:00,756
Perhaps you could be
a little more specific.

906
01:03:00,880 --> 01:03:04,873
McClane is here.
He's walking toward the bank.

907
01:03:05,960 --> 01:03:08,394
And the black man
is coming toward me.

908
01:03:08,520 --> 01:03:11,273
Oh, now that's a pity.

909
01:03:11,400 --> 01:03:13,755
And after we've gone to all
that trouble at the stadium.

910
01:03:13,880 --> 01:03:15,916
Simon, kill him.

911
01:03:16,040 --> 01:03:18,508
Stop toying with him
and kill him now.

912
01:03:19,600 --> 01:03:21,670
Okay. So be it.

913
01:03:21,800 --> 01:03:26,635
May he rest in peace.
I'll inform Karl in the lobby.

914
01:03:26,760 --> 01:03:29,513
- You pack up your team
and get out of there.
- And this one?

915
01:03:30,600 --> 01:03:32,397
Officer.

916
01:03:34,600 --> 01:03:37,114
Yeah, I'm, I'm, I'm afraid
I'm gonna need an answer on that issue.

917
01:03:42,280 --> 01:03:45,716
- Let him go.
- Understood. Yes, sir?

918
01:03:45,840 --> 01:03:48,400
John McClane says to give you this.

919
01:03:49,960 --> 01:03:52,394
Wait, wait.Jesus, don't open it.
It's a bomb.

920
01:03:52,520 --> 01:03:53,999
- Another?
- Yeah.

921
01:03:54,120 --> 01:03:56,839
Oh, I see. Um, oh,
we'll take care of that.

922
01:03:56,960 --> 01:03:59,269
We better move now. Sir,
thank you so much for your assistance.

923
01:03:59,400 --> 01:04:01,675
We really appreciate it.
Thank you.

924
01:04:04,520 --> 01:04:07,478
What are you doing?

925
01:04:09,320 --> 01:04:13,677
- I don't want to ride with it.
- Some kid could...

926
01:04:13,800 --> 01:04:15,756
Put it in the back.

927
01:04:20,920 --> 01:04:24,515
Hey! Y-You, you, uh,
leavin' this place unguarded?

928
01:04:33,240 --> 01:04:34,992
I understand.

929
01:04:44,520 --> 01:04:47,034
- How ya doin'?
- All right.

930
01:04:47,160 --> 01:04:49,674
John McClane. NYPD.

931
01:04:49,800 --> 01:04:54,316
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. It's laundry day.

932
01:04:55,400 --> 01:04:57,436
What can I do for you, Lieutenant?

933
01:04:57,560 --> 01:04:59,915
Has it been quiet like this
all morning here?

934
01:05:00,040 --> 01:05:03,271
- Well--
- Except for that big explosion
a couple of hours ago.

935
01:05:03,400 --> 01:05:06,358
I mean, have you seen anything strange
happen in the last hour or so?

936
01:05:06,480 --> 01:05:09,677
No. And we've had cops in here
pretty steady since the subway thing.

937
01:05:09,800 --> 01:05:11,438
Yeah.

938
01:05:11,560 --> 01:05:14,279
We were just gonna make a round on
the vault floor, if you wanna tag along.

939
01:05:14,400 --> 01:05:16,868
Sure. Yeah. I think I will.

940
01:05:17,000 --> 01:05:19,195
Now, what do you think of this heat
this late in the year?

941
01:05:19,320 --> 01:05:20,912
Eh, Indian summer, huh?

942
01:05:21,040 --> 01:05:24,271
Yeah, it feels like it's gonna rain
like dogs and cats later.

943
01:05:24,400 --> 01:05:28,552
- Here's one of your guys.
- Detective, uh, Otto, isn't it?

944
01:05:28,680 --> 01:05:30,477
John McClane.

945
01:05:33,000 --> 01:05:34,797
Hey, Mike. How ya doin'?

946
01:05:36,960 --> 01:05:40,589
I keep tellin' myself I'm gonna
take the stairs just for the exercise.

947
01:05:40,720 --> 01:05:42,676
And on a hot day like this.

948
01:05:42,800 --> 01:05:45,553
But it seems like I always end up
riding the lift.

949
01:06:11,560 --> 01:06:13,516
Hey, what was the lottery number
last night?

950
01:06:13,640 --> 01:06:16,757
Huh? Any of you guys
play the lottery? No?

951
01:06:16,880 --> 01:06:19,758
Ah, my wife buys me two tickets
every week.

952
01:06:19,880 --> 01:06:21,836
For the last ten years,
plays the same two numbers all the time.

953
01:06:21,960 --> 01:06:23,791
I said, ''Honey, why don't you play
a different number?''

954
01:06:23,920 --> 01:06:26,309
She goes,
''Well, those are my lucky numbers.''

955
01:06:26,440 --> 01:06:28,556
I got the tickets right here.

956
01:06:30,400 --> 01:06:34,075
Put that fuckin' gun down!
Put that fuckin' gun down now!

957
01:06:40,520 --> 01:06:42,317
Put it down!

958
01:06:47,560 --> 01:06:49,551
Hello!

959
01:06:49,680 --> 01:06:51,716
Anybody down here?

960
01:07:01,680 --> 01:07:03,591
- Put your hands up!
Put your fuckin' hands up now!
- No, no, no!

961
01:07:03,720 --> 01:07:06,154
John, no!
No! God, it's me! It's me!

962
01:07:08,400 --> 01:07:11,119
-Jesus Christ,
you almost gave me a heart attack.
- You all right?

963
01:07:11,240 --> 01:07:12,639
- Huh?
- You all right?

964
01:07:12,760 --> 01:07:14,876
- Yeah, yeah. It's not my blood.
- What the hell's goin' on down here?

965
01:07:15,000 --> 01:07:16,797
Go take a look in there.

966
01:07:39,000 --> 01:07:42,549
Hey, McClane.
Where the hell is everybody?

967
01:07:42,680 --> 01:07:44,557
Simon fuckin' says!

968
01:07:46,200 --> 01:07:49,033
I should've seen it comin' a mile away.
This was never about revenge.

969
01:07:49,160 --> 01:07:52,197
- It's about a goddam heist.
- Wh-Wh-What was in the room?

970
01:07:52,320 --> 01:07:55,710
- This.
- What is this?

971
01:07:55,840 --> 01:07:58,149
- Oh, shit! Is this gold?
- Yeah, it's gold.

972
01:07:58,280 --> 01:08:01,113
Damn, this is heavy!
They cleaned out a whole room of this?

973
01:08:01,240 --> 01:08:05,233
- Yeah.
- You know, that would've taken
like a, a, a, a tank, or a, or a, a--

974
01:08:05,360 --> 01:08:07,510
A dump truck.

975
01:08:07,640 --> 01:08:09,676
Fourteen great big dump trucks.

976
01:08:09,800 --> 01:08:11,916
- We almost got hit by a dump truck.
- Shit!

977
01:08:12,040 --> 01:08:14,554
- Damn. Slow down! Shit!
- Put that shit down.

978
01:08:14,680 --> 01:08:16,636
- No fuckin' way.
- They ain't gonna let you keep it.

979
01:08:16,760 --> 01:08:18,876
- Yeah, yeah, we'll see.
- We're gonna need a car.

980
01:08:19,000 --> 01:08:20,592
A car?

981
01:08:25,640 --> 01:08:28,950
- You know how to hot-wire this thing?
- Of course I can. I'm an electrician.

982
01:08:29,080 --> 01:08:30,877
Only problem is...

983
01:08:34,480 --> 01:08:36,471
takes too fuckin' long.

984
01:08:48,120 --> 01:08:51,908
- Not on the bridge!
- Down there, McClane. The FDR.

985
01:08:55,080 --> 01:08:56,877
Let's go, let's go. Come on!

986
01:08:58,280 --> 01:09:00,714
- Oh, shit!
- What?

987
01:09:00,840 --> 01:09:03,274
- They shot the phone.
- Oh, too bad.

988
01:09:03,400 --> 01:09:05,994
- Come on. What's 21out of 42?
- I don't have a clue.

989
01:09:06,120 --> 01:09:09,829
- Well, what about Yankee stadium?
- We'll get there, but that son of
a bitch is not gettin' off of Manhattan.

990
01:09:09,960 --> 01:09:11,757
- Move!
-Jesus Christ!

991
01:09:11,880 --> 01:09:13,359
Who do you think you are, lady,
Hillary Clinton?

992
01:09:13,480 --> 01:09:15,152
- That's it! Hillary Clinton.
- What?

993
01:09:15,280 --> 01:09:17,840
- The 42nd president.
- No. She'd be the 43rd president.

994
01:09:17,960 --> 01:09:21,999
- All right, all right.
But who's the 21st?
- I don't know.

995
01:09:22,120 --> 01:09:23,917
- You don't know?
- No, I don't know! Do you know?

996
01:09:24,040 --> 01:09:25,996
- No!
- Well?

997
01:09:26,120 --> 01:09:28,156
What kind of engine does this piece
of shit have? Come on, step on it!

998
01:09:28,280 --> 01:09:31,352
It's a Yugo. It's built
for economy, not speed.

999
01:09:33,680 --> 01:09:35,989
- Whoa! What are you doin'?
- I'm gonna get us another phone.

1000
01:09:39,160 --> 01:09:41,515
Wait, wait, wait!
Wait, wait, wait!

1001
01:09:41,640 --> 01:09:44,837
- Hey, who was the 21st president?
- Go fuck yourself!

1002
01:09:46,920 --> 01:09:50,469
- That guy was pissed.
- He'll feel better
when he looks in the back seat.

1003
01:09:50,600 --> 01:09:52,556
Oh, shit.
That was my gold bar!

1004
01:09:52,680 --> 01:09:55,148
This is McClane.
Get me Inspector Walter Cobb.

1005
01:09:55,280 --> 01:09:58,477
-John, where the hell are you?
- Walter, it's not a revenge.
It's a heist.

1006
01:09:58,600 --> 01:10:01,990
- What?
- There's gold in the Federal Reserve,
and they took a shitload of it.

1007
01:10:02,120 --> 01:10:05,510
- They're headed north in dump trucks.
- Have you been drinking, McClane?

1008
01:10:05,640 --> 01:10:07,437
No, not since this morning.

1009
01:10:07,560 --> 01:10:10,313
Listen. There's a line of dump trucks
northbound on the FDR at about 70th.

1010
01:10:10,440 --> 01:10:12,954
You gotta close the bridge and get some
helicopters over there right away.

1011
01:10:13,080 --> 01:10:15,196
I couldn't close a hot dog stand
right now.

1012
01:10:15,320 --> 01:10:18,118
I'm spread all over hell.
What about this damn bomb?

1013
01:10:18,240 --> 01:10:20,708
Find out who the 21st president was.
It's got somethin' to do with this.

1014
01:10:20,840 --> 01:10:22,512
John!John, the 21st what?

1015
01:10:22,640 --> 01:10:26,474
Walter! Shit!
Goddam cellular fuckin' phones!

1016
01:10:26,600 --> 01:10:28,397
- Get hold of Munson in Triborough.
- Inspector.

1017
01:10:28,520 --> 01:10:31,398
Tell him to close all the East River
bridges north of 59th Street.

1018
01:10:31,520 --> 01:10:33,397
- Lookin' for dump trucks.
- Dump trucks?

1019
01:10:33,520 --> 01:10:37,229
McClane says there are dump trucks
headed up the FDR loaded with gold.

1020
01:10:37,360 --> 01:10:40,477
Walter, they don't allow
dump trucks on the FDR!

1021
01:10:40,600 --> 01:10:42,670
- Connie!
- All right.
You don't want I should argue.

1022
01:10:42,800 --> 01:10:45,109
I won't argue,
no matter how stupid it is.

1023
01:10:45,240 --> 01:10:48,073
K-9, bring it around to the back.
Check out the boiler room.

1024
01:10:48,200 --> 01:10:49,952
Find anything, Charlie?

1025
01:10:50,080 --> 01:10:53,152
I could spend a week in here with
an X-ray machine and still not find it.

1026
01:10:53,280 --> 01:10:56,431
You don't have a week, Charlie.
You got five more minutes. Then
we're movin' up to 86th Street.

1027
01:10:56,560 --> 01:10:58,790
We're goin' as fast as we can.

1028
01:10:58,920 --> 01:11:00,399
What's up?

1029
01:11:00,520 --> 01:11:03,876
McClane was mentioning something
about the Federal Reserve Building.

1030
01:11:04,000 --> 01:11:07,436
- Isn't that right near that Wall Street
bomb site we just left?
- Yeah.

1031
01:11:13,480 --> 01:11:15,596
How long do you want us
to stay here?

1032
01:11:15,720 --> 01:11:18,154
The men at the stadium.
Stay or go?

1033
01:11:18,280 --> 01:11:20,430
Karl should have checked in by now.

1034
01:11:20,560 --> 01:11:22,596
Moment.

1035
01:11:29,320 --> 01:11:31,311
Come on. Come on.

1036
01:11:32,680 --> 01:11:35,797
Stay where you are.
McClane may still turn up.

1037
01:11:36,880 --> 01:11:40,395
Relax, Targo.
If he is still alive...

1038
01:11:40,520 --> 01:11:42,829
he won't be talking to anyone.

1039
01:11:42,960 --> 01:11:44,279
It's the next turn-off.

1040
01:11:45,640 --> 01:11:47,756
Hi. It's Elvis Duran.
You're on the air. What's up?

1041
01:11:47,880 --> 01:11:50,792
First of all, I just wanna tell you
what a great show you got.

1042
01:11:50,920 --> 01:11:53,673
- I listen to you all the time.
- Thank you. Thank you.
What do you wanna talk about?

1043
01:11:53,800 --> 01:11:56,792
Well,you know all those cop cars
screamin'around everywhere?

1044
01:11:56,920 --> 01:12:00,151
You know what they're up to?
There's a bomb in a school.

1045
01:12:00,280 --> 01:12:02,430
- My cousin's a cop.
- Here you go, my dear.

1046
01:12:02,560 --> 01:12:04,869
Somebody put a big bomb
in a school somewhere.

1047
01:12:05,000 --> 01:12:07,275
- Seven. Five.
- Only they don't know which one.

1048
01:12:07,400 --> 01:12:09,356
- 207--
- So they're searching all of them.

1049
01:12:09,480 --> 01:12:12,392
- Shh. Shh.
- Every school in the metropolitan area.

1050
01:12:12,520 --> 01:12:14,636
Holy shit.

1051
01:12:14,760 --> 01:12:16,079
- Doris!
- Annie?

1052
01:12:16,200 --> 01:12:17,269
Doris, can you get ahold
of my wife?

1053
01:12:18,400 --> 01:12:22,518
Turley! Half the goddam city
just called 9-1-1!

1054
01:12:25,160 --> 01:12:26,832
- They're gone.
- What?

1055
01:12:26,960 --> 01:12:29,030
- They're gone!
- Who is this guy, Houdini?

1056
01:12:29,160 --> 01:12:31,276
Shit! Down there! Down there!

1057
01:12:33,000 --> 01:12:36,549
-This thing got air bags?
-Your side does. I don't know about my--

1058
01:12:37,640 --> 01:12:39,437
McClane!

1059
01:12:58,600 --> 01:13:00,477
In the truck,
let me see the hands.

1060
01:13:01,800 --> 01:13:03,597
Put 'em on the door!

1061
01:13:07,360 --> 01:13:09,635
Don't kill me! Don't shoot me!

1062
01:13:11,240 --> 01:13:13,037
- You a truck driver?
- No, I'm a beautician.

1063
01:13:13,160 --> 01:13:15,435
Of course I'm a truck driver!

1064
01:13:16,520 --> 01:13:19,671
- Where are you takin' this truck?
- The aqueduct.

1065
01:13:19,800 --> 01:13:21,518
What are you takin' a dump truck
to the race track for?

1066
01:13:21,640 --> 01:13:26,236
- No, the aqueduct. The aque--
The water aqueduct!
- Aqueduct?

1067
01:13:28,600 --> 01:13:32,878
See? Goes from here all the way up
to the Catskill Mountains.

1068
01:13:33,000 --> 01:13:34,877
- What does?
- That! The water pipe!

1069
01:13:35,000 --> 01:13:37,195
Goes for about 60 miles.

1070
01:13:44,040 --> 01:13:45,359
- Hey, you the foreman?
- Yeah.

1071
01:13:45,480 --> 01:13:49,837
NYPD. You had any, like,
extra dump trucks come through here
in the last couple of minutes?

1072
01:13:49,960 --> 01:13:51,791
I'm gonna write
those fuckin' clowns up.

1073
01:13:51,920 --> 01:13:54,070
They better start
payin' attention to work orders,
or we're gonna kick some butt.

1074
01:13:54,200 --> 01:13:57,351
- Who? Who are you talkin' about?
- Ah, the dozen idiots
who tore ass up the tube!

1075
01:13:57,480 --> 01:14:00,313
We're not loadin' up there any more.
We're loadin' over here.

1076
01:14:00,440 --> 01:14:02,476
So much for bridges and helicopters.

1077
01:14:02,600 --> 01:14:04,477
You got a map that shows me
where this tunnel goes?

1078
01:14:04,600 --> 01:14:06,397
Yeah. Right here.

1079
01:14:08,120 --> 01:14:11,669
We run pretty much up
under the Saw Mill
till you get up to the Coffer Dam.

1080
01:14:11,800 --> 01:14:14,519
From there on, we've already brought
the water down from the reservoir.

1081
01:14:14,640 --> 01:14:18,792
- Anybody get in or outta there?
- Yeah. There's a vent shaft
every two miles.

1082
01:14:18,920 --> 01:14:20,353
- No. I mean with a truck.
- At the Coffer Dam.

1083
01:14:20,480 --> 01:14:22,755
You can get a truck in there.
You can get there on the surface.

1084
01:14:22,880 --> 01:14:25,997
Just follow the Saw Mill River Parkway
up there. It's about 20 miles.

1085
01:14:26,120 --> 01:14:27,917
All right. I'm gonna meet you
right there, all right?

1086
01:14:28,040 --> 01:14:29,553
Wait, wait!
Wh-What am I supposed to do?

1087
01:14:29,680 --> 01:14:32,592
- You're gonna go up to Yankee Stadium.
- McClane!

1088
01:14:32,720 --> 01:14:34,551
Go! Get outta here.
We got less than two hours.

1089
01:14:34,680 --> 01:14:36,432
Goddam it!

1090
01:14:41,360 --> 01:14:43,590
Hey! Is somethin' wrong?

1091
01:14:43,720 --> 01:14:46,075
480 yards of rock moved so far.

1092
01:14:46,200 --> 01:14:48,191
Now, that's ten times
the Hoover Dam.

1093
01:14:48,320 --> 01:14:52,108
Right now, there's 516 feet of rock
above our heads.

1094
01:14:52,240 --> 01:14:54,879
This part is phase three
of tunnel three.

1095
01:14:55,000 --> 01:14:57,958
Planning for it began
back in 1954...

1096
01:14:58,080 --> 01:15:00,753
but construction didn't begin
till June of 19 70.

1097
01:15:00,880 --> 01:15:03,235
You know what the most interesting part
of tunnel three is?

1098
01:15:03,360 --> 01:15:05,749
- What's that,Jerry?
- The valves. Each one--

1099
01:15:12,280 --> 01:15:16,558
A big departure
from tunnels one and two.

1100
01:15:16,680 --> 01:15:19,956
Come on! What a hell of a place
to break down.

1101
01:15:20,080 --> 01:15:22,799
Hold it a minute,Jerry.
Let me have your hard hat.

1102
01:15:22,920 --> 01:15:25,559
- You got a jacket?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah. Here.

1103
01:15:25,680 --> 01:15:27,716
Wait here a minute.

1104
01:15:27,840 --> 01:15:30,354
Wait until he gets
alongside the door.

