Go! Go! Go! Hip-hop! Hip-hop!
Come on. Everybody! Let's go!

1327
01:35:22,360 --> 01:35:23,918
- Run! Run! Run! Run! Run! Run!
- Keep moving.

1328
01:35:24,040 --> 01:35:28,158
- We're gonna win! We're gonna win!
- Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

1329
01:35:28,280 --> 01:35:29,679
Keep moving!
To your left! To your left!

1330
01:35:41,240 --> 01:35:45,279
What are they doin'?
Yo, where you goin'?

1331
01:35:45,400 --> 01:35:47,311
- Hey, where you goin'?
- What's goin' on?

1332
01:35:47,440 --> 01:35:51,433
I see you all day, little man.
Policeman.

1333
01:35:52,880 --> 01:35:55,440
And you don't go away.

1334
01:35:55,560 --> 01:35:57,551
Yeah, I'm that fuckin'
Energizer bunny.

1335
01:36:00,040 --> 01:36:02,349
Where are you going now, huh?

1336
01:36:04,640 --> 01:36:07,757
Going to arrest me, ''bunny''?

1337
01:36:07,880 --> 01:36:09,632
No.

1338
01:36:09,760 --> 01:36:12,513
I don't think
I'm gonna arrest you.

1339
01:36:12,640 --> 01:36:14,949
I'm gonna fuckin'--

1340
01:36:24,840 --> 01:36:26,910
I knew it was bullshit.
There's nobody watchin'.

1341
01:36:27,040 --> 01:36:28,837
Time to get Charlie out.

1342
01:36:28,960 --> 01:36:32,077
- Let's move, Charles. Time's up.
- Give me another 30 seconds.

1343
01:36:32,200 --> 01:36:34,236
Takes a minute-15
if you're a kid, Charlie.

1344
01:36:34,360 --> 01:36:36,715
And last I looked, you weren't too light
on your feet. Now move!

1345
01:36:37,880 --> 01:36:40,394
- Up here!
- Help us!
- Oh, my God!

1346
01:36:40,520 --> 01:36:42,317
- Come on!
- Look over here!

1347
01:36:42,440 --> 01:36:44,556
- Christ, get 'em outta there!
- Rooms are locked!

1348
01:36:44,680 --> 01:36:47,114
- The rooms are locked!
- Get outta the way!

1349
01:36:47,240 --> 01:36:51,756
Hey! Any one marked four!

1350
01:36:51,880 --> 01:36:53,632
What's goin' on, Walter?

1351
01:36:53,760 --> 01:36:56,035
We still have kids
in the building.

1352
01:37:00,840 --> 01:37:03,673
- I'm stayin'.
- No, Charlie. Get outta there.

1353
01:37:05,520 --> 01:37:08,239
You ever see that show
called The Addams Family?

1354
01:37:08,360 --> 01:37:10,999
They got a motherfucker on there
called Lurch.

1355
01:37:11,120 --> 01:37:13,270
You don't think I'm gonna let you
get to that gun, do you?

1356
01:37:18,080 --> 01:37:19,399
Fuck!

1357
01:37:37,960 --> 01:37:39,996
Help! Help! Help!

1358
01:37:40,120 --> 01:37:42,076
Four! Fuck it!
Get outta the way!

1359
01:37:53,800 --> 01:37:56,234
- Where are they, Walter?
- Still in.

1360
01:38:02,440 --> 01:38:04,715
No guts, no glory.

1361
01:38:07,440 --> 01:38:10,477
If we get to the roof,
we can jump to the next building!

1362
01:38:10,600 --> 01:38:13,672
- Shit!
- Outta the way.

1363
01:38:13,800 --> 01:38:16,951
Okay. Come on.

1364
01:38:17,080 --> 01:38:19,116
Get him up here. Get him up here!
Come on! Come on!

1365
01:38:19,240 --> 01:38:22,869
Mayday, mayday. Bridgeport Coast Guard.
Bridgeport Coast Guard, come in.

1366
01:38:35,760 --> 01:38:37,557
Come on, kids.

1367
01:38:41,760 --> 01:38:44,354
- Shit, it's too far!
- Over here. Down.

1368
01:38:50,520 --> 01:38:51,839
No guts, no glory.

1369
01:38:52,840 --> 01:38:54,796
There's a big black-and-white fuckin'
boat in the middle of the harbour.

1370
01:38:54,920 --> 01:38:57,354
- Please stay on the line.
- Yeah, sure. I'll stay on the line.

1371
01:39:15,080 --> 01:39:16,877
Pancake syrup?

1372
01:39:17,160 --> 01:39:18,798
Stupid, stupid--

1373
01:39:22,080 --> 01:39:23,752
Hello,John McClane.

1374
01:39:25,160 --> 01:39:27,116
There was never any bomb
in the school, was there?

1375
01:39:27,240 --> 01:39:29,549
Of course not.

1376
01:39:29,680 --> 01:39:32,114
I'm a soldier, not a monster...

1377
01:39:32,240 --> 01:39:35,152
even though I sometimes work
for monsters.

1378
01:39:35,280 --> 01:39:38,033
No. The real bomb is on this ship.

1379
01:39:42,160 --> 01:39:44,594
Coast Guard.

1380
01:39:44,720 --> 01:39:49,669
I was tellin' 'em where the boat was.
Game over, huh?

1381
01:39:49,800 --> 01:39:52,792
Not quite over.

1382
01:39:52,920 --> 01:39:55,912
Bridgeport Coast Guard.
Come in, please.

1383
01:39:56,040 --> 01:39:58,679
They put you on hold?

1384
01:39:58,800 --> 01:40:00,597
She told me to stay on the line.

1385
01:40:04,880 --> 01:40:08,111
- Oh, God, I love this country.
- You know, your brother was an asshole.

1386
01:40:10,760 --> 01:40:12,830
- You know, he really was an asshole.
- He was-- He was an asshole.

1387
01:40:12,960 --> 01:40:16,714
You, you got his number, yeah?
Yeah, okay.

1388
01:40:18,760 --> 01:40:22,150
Forgive me.
Would you help Mr McClane below?

1389
01:40:23,600 --> 01:40:25,716
Careful now.

1390
01:40:26,960 --> 01:40:30,316
Now, do you have the communique?

1391
01:40:30,440 --> 01:40:32,192
Bridgeport radio,
come in, please. Bridgeport.

1392
01:40:32,320 --> 01:40:34,072
- Coast Guard.
- Are you there, dear?

1393
01:40:34,200 --> 01:40:37,988
- Yes, we're here.
- Do you have the ability
to record a message?

1394
01:40:38,120 --> 01:40:40,076
- Yes.
- Then please begin now.

1395
01:40:40,200 --> 01:40:41,519
Right.

1396
01:40:46,440 --> 01:40:49,034
This is a communique
from the CRF.

1397
01:40:49,160 --> 01:40:52,835
For too long, the West has conspired
to steal the wealth of the world...

1398
01:40:52,960 --> 01:40:56,509
consigning the balance of humanity
to economic starvation.

1399
01:40:56,640 --> 01:40:59,359
Today, we will level
the playing field.

1400
01:40:59,480 --> 01:41:02,552
In a few minutes, the contents
of the Federal Reserve Bank--

1401
01:41:02,680 --> 01:41:05,274
the gold your economies
are built on--

1402
01:41:05,400 --> 01:41:08,198
will be redistributed by explosive...

1403
01:41:08,320 --> 01:41:10,197
across the bottom
of the Long Island Sound.

1404
01:41:11,760 --> 01:41:15,150
If you are not in gridlock,
I invite you to come and watch.

1405
01:41:19,880 --> 01:41:22,838
- You're gonna blow it all up?
- That's the idea.

1406
01:41:22,960 --> 01:41:24,757
There are some gentlemen
in the Middle East...

1407
01:41:24,880 --> 01:41:27,474
who seem to think that they'll make
a great deal of money.

1408
01:41:27,600 --> 01:41:31,115
See the men safely off the ship, and
I'll see you in the port-side launch.

1409
01:41:32,200 --> 01:41:34,634
The hell's all this
got to do with killin' McClane?

1410
01:41:36,200 --> 01:41:38,350
Life has its little bonuses.

1411
01:41:38,480 --> 01:41:40,755
Didn't I hear you say
you didn't even like your brother?

1412
01:41:40,880 --> 01:41:42,950
There's a difference, you know,
between not liking one's brother...

1413
01:41:43,080 --> 01:41:46,470
and not caring when some dumb Irish
flatfoot drops him out of a window.

1414
01:41:46,600 --> 01:41:48,477
Hey, I didn't even know
that motherfucker!

1415
01:41:48,600 --> 01:41:50,795
Yes, and I never invited you
aboard this ship.

1416
01:41:50,920 --> 01:41:52,433
No riddle is gonna stop
this motherfucker?

1417
01:41:52,560 --> 01:41:55,279
No code, no riddle,
no fancy little countdown.

1418
01:41:55,400 --> 01:41:58,949
Hey, fuck-head.
Yeah, you. Fuck-head.

1419
01:42:00,400 --> 01:42:03,676
There's just one thing
I gotta know.

1420
01:42:03,800 --> 01:42:08,430
You got any aspirins? I've had
a bad fuckin' headache all day long.

1421
01:42:11,240 --> 01:42:12,878
Must be your lucky day.

1422
01:42:14,280 --> 01:42:15,759
Keep the bottle.

1423
01:42:27,600 --> 01:42:29,397
Where is the gold?

1424
01:42:31,800 --> 01:42:33,836
He's betrayed us.

1425
01:42:33,960 --> 01:42:36,520
The containers
are filled with that.

1426
01:43:07,800 --> 01:43:10,030
If I hadn't have saved your fuckin' ass,
I wouldn't be sittin' here with you...

1427
01:43:10,160 --> 01:43:12,390
about to blow up with $100 billion
in fuckin' gold!

1428
01:43:12,520 --> 01:43:14,954
Yeah, well, I got some bad news.
You're only gonna blow up with me.

1429
01:43:15,080 --> 01:43:16,718
- What?
- There's no gold on this boat.

1430
01:43:16,840 --> 01:43:19,593
- How do you know that?
- 'Cause I know the man.
I know the family.

1431
01:43:19,720 --> 01:43:24,271
The only thing better than blowin' up
$100 billion worth of gold is makin'
people think you did.

1432
01:43:24,400 --> 01:43:27,392
- Yeah? Well, where is it?
- I don't know. He must have switched it
back on the dock somewhere.

1433
01:43:27,520 --> 01:43:29,317
Oh, yeah. That's supposed
to make me feel better?

1434
01:43:29,440 --> 01:43:32,432
No. You're wrong about the other thing,
though. You're not gonna die.

1435
01:43:32,560 --> 01:43:35,552
Yeah? You know
some cop trick about handcuffs
that's gonna get us outta this?

1436
01:43:35,680 --> 01:43:38,194
Yeah. Use a key.

1437
01:43:38,320 --> 01:43:40,595
- You know how to pick this lock?
- Is this some black shit again?

1438
01:43:40,720 --> 01:43:43,109
Will you stop with that racial shit?
Are you a fuckin' locksmith or not?

1439
01:43:43,240 --> 01:43:45,754
Yeah, yeah, yeah. I can do it
if I had somethin' to do it with.

1440
01:43:45,880 --> 01:43:48,872
- How about a splinter
of that cable I slid down?
- That might work.

1441
01:43:51,720 --> 01:43:53,995
- Hold on.
- Fuck are you doin'?

1442
01:43:57,160 --> 01:44:00,789
Oh, fuck! Shit!
How's that? That big enough?

1443
01:44:00,920 --> 01:44:02,956
Shit. Yeah.
Yeah, that might work.

1444
01:44:03,080 --> 01:44:06,038
All right. Then I'm gonna drop it
in your hands. Cup your hands.

1445
01:44:06,160 --> 01:44:07,912
Don't drop this motherfucker,
all right?

1446
01:44:08,040 --> 01:44:10,918
- Get, get it right. Come on. One--
- You ready? Ready?

1447
01:44:11,040 --> 01:44:13,031
Two-- Spit it.

1448
01:44:13,160 --> 01:44:16,391
- Yeah! Get it?
- Come on. Come on. Move your hands.

1449
01:44:16,520 --> 01:44:18,875
All right. Okay.

1450
01:44:19,000 --> 01:44:21,275
Damn, McClane. You know,
I was just startin' to like you.

1451
01:44:21,400 --> 01:44:24,870
- Yeah? Well, don't. I'm an asshole.
- What are you talkin' about now?

1452
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:27,798
- I lied to you, Zeus.
- About what?

1453
01:44:27,920 --> 01:44:30,718
You remember I said
Weiss found that bomb up in Harlem?

1454
01:44:30,840 --> 01:44:32,558
- Yeah.
- They found it down in Chinatown.

1455
01:44:32,680 --> 01:44:35,433
Oh, now that's low--
even for a white motherfucker like you.

1456
01:44:35,560 --> 01:44:37,915
I told you I was an asshole.

1457
01:44:38,040 --> 01:44:40,076
What the fuck was that?

1458
01:44:40,200 --> 01:44:42,555
I don't know.

1459
01:44:42,680 --> 01:44:44,671
Look, it was the only way
I could get you to come with me.

1460
01:44:44,800 --> 01:44:46,870
Uh-huh.
You got a wife, McClane?

1461
01:44:47,000 --> 01:44:49,992
- Yeah.
- I'm surprised anybody'd stay with you
long enough to be married.

1462
01:44:50,120 --> 01:44:53,157
Yeah. Well, she didn't stick around
too long. We're sorta separated.

1463
01:44:53,280 --> 01:44:54,759
What the fuck is ''sorta separated''?

1464
01:44:54,880 --> 01:44:57,678
Well, she was in LA,
I was in New York.

1465
01:44:57,800 --> 01:45:01,315
Had a fight on the phone. She hung up.
I didn't call her back.

1466
01:45:01,440 --> 01:45:04,671
- How long ago was that?
- About a year ago now.

1467
01:45:04,800 --> 01:45:06,597
About a yea--

1468
01:45:08,200 --> 01:45:10,794
What the fuck
are you laughin' about?

1469
01:45:10,920 --> 01:45:14,549
You threw away your marriage
because you were too fuckin' stupid
to pick up the phone?

1470
01:45:14,680 --> 01:45:16,830
What, you think that's funny, huh?
You laugh at other people's misfortunes?

1471
01:45:16,960 --> 01:45:18,678
I bet you blame that shit
on your wife too, right?

1472
01:45:18,800 --> 01:45:20,870
Well, my wife
is a very stubborn woman, yes.

1473
01:45:23,640 --> 01:45:26,029
You better stop fuckin' laughin'
and undo these cuffs.

1474
01:45:26,160 --> 01:45:28,196
I'm almost there!

1475
01:45:28,320 --> 01:45:30,709
There! How's that for concentration?
Oh, shit!

1476
01:45:30,840 --> 01:45:32,398
- What?
- Fuck! I dropped the thing!

1477
01:45:32,520 --> 01:45:35,080
- Dropped the fucking thing?
- Goddam it!

1478
01:45:35,200 --> 01:45:37,430
- Shit! Where is it? Where did it go?
- Find it. Find it, all right?

1479
01:45:37,560 --> 01:45:40,120
I don't fuckin' see it.

1480
01:45:41,200 --> 01:45:43,760
What the fuck is that?

1481
01:45:43,880 --> 01:45:46,599
I think I made it mad.

1482
01:45:46,720 --> 01:45:48,199
Just go, McClane.
Get the fuck out of here.

1483
01:45:48,320 --> 01:45:51,437
- Gotta fuckin' do somethin'!
- Goddam it, McClane! Listen to me!

1484
01:45:52,680 --> 01:45:54,955
Just go.

1485
01:45:55,080 --> 01:45:57,674
Have a hard enough time gettin' through
the day without havin' your death
on my conscience, man.

1486
01:45:57,800 --> 01:45:59,711
- Shut the fuck up and think, all right?
- Okay, okay.

1487
01:45:59,840 --> 01:46:02,673
- Tools. Tools. Check the engine room.
- There's no time!

1488
01:46:03,880 --> 01:46:05,677
- What the hell's it doin' now?
- It's mixin'.

1489
01:46:05,800 --> 01:46:07,279
Shit!

1490
01:46:08,840 --> 01:46:10,637
- What the hell are you doin'?
- Get ready. Lean forward.

1491
01:46:10,760 --> 01:46:13,115
- What?
- Lean forward, goddam it!

1492
01:46:13,240 --> 01:46:15,151
What? The fuck you doin'?

1493
01:46:15,280 --> 01:46:17,032
Now it's gonna go fast.
Lean forward.

1494
01:46:17,160 --> 01:46:19,628
- Oh, no, no!
- Lean forward! Get ready!
Move your hands!

1495
01:46:19,760 --> 01:46:22,115
Damn! Motherfuckin' shit!

1496
01:46:22,240 --> 01:46:25,198
- Come on. Let's go!
- Oh, goddam! Goddam!

1497
01:46:25,320 --> 01:46:28,278
- Come on! Come on!
- Oh, fuck! My leg! Ow!

1498
01:46:29,440 --> 01:46:33,558
Get upstairs! Come on!
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Get upstairs!

1499
01:46:34,680 --> 01:46:36,875
Oh, shit! Ow! Damn it! My foot!

1500
01:46:37,000 --> 01:46:38,672
- Let's go! Let's go!
- Down there at the back of the boat.
Come on!

1501
01:46:38,800 --> 01:46:41,234
- No, damn it!
- Run, goddam it!

1502
01:46:41,360 --> 01:46:43,351
- I am, you--
- Come on!

1503
01:46:43,480 --> 01:46:45,357
- All right? Watch! Watch! Watch!
- Yeah.

1504
01:46:45,480 --> 01:46:47,675
Let's go! Down here!
The back of the--

1505
01:47:14,640 --> 01:47:15,993
How's he doin'?

1506
01:47:16,120 --> 01:47:18,554
I got shot in the leg.
How do ya think I'm doin'?

1507
01:47:18,680 --> 01:47:21,478
- He's gonna be just fine.
- How about you?

1508
01:47:21,600 --> 01:47:24,398
I'm all right.
Did ya get Ricky out of there?

1509
01:47:26,160 --> 01:47:27,957
Yeah, they found him.

1510
01:47:29,400 --> 01:47:32,551
- Are you gonna be all right?
- Got a bad headache.

1511
01:47:32,680 --> 01:47:35,240
- Think they're mad at me?
- I wouldn't worry about them.

1512
01:47:35,360 --> 01:47:38,750
They'll get to you eventually,
but right now they're busy with
this salvage operation, I guess.

1513
01:47:38,880 --> 01:47:41,997
No! Dre-Dredges! Dredges!

1514
01:47:42,120 --> 01:47:44,076
They're just wastin' their time.
There's no gold out there.

1515
01:47:44,200 --> 01:47:46,031
- What do you mean?
- He took it with him.

1516
01:47:46,160 --> 01:47:49,357
- He beat me.
-John, he beat all of us.

1517
01:47:49,480 --> 01:47:51,994
- He wasn't playin' against you.
- Fuck that, McClane.

1518
01:47:52,120 --> 01:47:55,192
You're still alive, aren't ya?

1519
01:47:55,320 --> 01:47:57,914
- Well, aren't ya?
- Yeah.

1520
01:47:58,040 --> 01:48:00,600
So he lost. Lambert.

1521
01:48:00,720 --> 01:48:03,188
Would you give him a quarter?

1522
01:48:03,320 --> 01:48:04,878
Asshole.

1523
01:48:07,160 --> 01:48:08,957
- Take it easy.
- I got him.
- That's it.

1524
01:48:09,080 --> 01:48:10,672
- Easy.
- Yeah, this is collect from John.

1525
01:48:10,800 --> 01:48:13,075
Thanks, guys. Appreciate this.

1526
01:48:18,200 --> 01:48:21,192
Yeah, uh, Carmine, just tell him
you'll accept the charges.

1527
01:48:21,320 --> 01:48:24,118
Son of a bitch had aspirin.

1528
01:48:24,240 --> 01:48:26,151
Yeah, it's John.
Yeah, I'm hangin' in there.

1529
01:48:26,280 --> 01:48:28,396
Is Holly there?
Yeah, I'll hold on.

1530
01:48:44,520 --> 01:48:46,112
Zeus, hold up! Whoa!

1531
01:48:46,240 --> 01:48:50,677
John? John? John?
Goddam it,you son of a--

1532
01:49:16,960 --> 01:49:18,871
Yesterday--

1533
01:49:19,000 --> 01:49:22,595
Yesterday we were an army
with no country.

1534
01:49:22,720 --> 01:49:26,235
Tomorrow, we have to decide...

1535
01:49:27,320 --> 01:49:29,629
which country we want to buy.

1536
01:49:34,400 --> 01:49:37,995
And remember,
this is all due...

1537
01:49:38,120 --> 01:49:43,353
to the g-g-g-g-g-g-g-g-gullibility
of the New York Police Department.

1538
01:49:46,480 --> 01:49:48,869
To fallen comrades.

1539
01:50:13,160 --> 01:50:15,151
Leutnant, take over.

1540
01:50:15,280 --> 01:50:17,191
All right. Listen up!
First squad...

1541
01:50:17,320 --> 01:50:19,709
you muster up in half an hour
in the school bus!

1542
01:50:19,840 --> 01:50:21,398
You'll be the lacrosse team!

1543
01:50:21,520 --> 01:50:24,990
The plane's in Nova Scotia.
We can leave in twenty minutes.

1544
01:50:32,880 --> 01:50:34,393
No rush.

1545
01:50:34,520 --> 01:50:38,877
And,Jurgen,
you'll be the Padre!

1546
01:50:39,000 --> 01:50:40,319
Padre?

1547
01:51:02,720 --> 01:51:04,517
Lights! Douse those lights!

1548
01:51:26,520 --> 01:51:30,433
Hey, dick-head.!
Did I come at a bad time?

1549
01:51:35,560 --> 01:51:38,597
Whoa! I think
she's pissed at you, McClane!

1550
01:51:47,880 --> 01:51:50,235
Go! Go!

1551
01:51:58,560 --> 01:52:00,312
He's under us right now. Come on
back around. Come on back around.

1552
01:52:00,440 --> 01:52:02,510
- That's right. Run, motherfuckers.
- Zeus, what've we got on your side?

1553
01:52:02,640 --> 01:52:04,437
Look like roaches
with the lights comin' on.

1554
01:52:06,920 --> 01:52:10,549
- Are we going to Nova Scotia?
- You go with the trucks!

1555
01:52:10,680 --> 01:52:12,830
I have something personal
to finish.

1556
01:52:15,640 --> 01:52:17,437
Let's go to work!

1557
01:52:18,960 --> 01:52:20,871
Come on! Move it!

1558
01:52:30,360 --> 01:52:33,591
That's right. Run, motherfuckers!
The exterminators are here!

1559
01:52:45,160 --> 01:52:48,948
What the fuck? Oh, shit!
What the fuck is this smoke back here?

1560
01:52:49,080 --> 01:52:51,719
We got a chopper behind us.
You got a gun on board?

1561
01:52:51,840 --> 01:52:54,035
What is this?

1562
01:52:56,400 --> 01:52:59,437
Can't see a goddam thing. Hold it
still. I can't see a goddam thing.

1563
01:53:03,240 --> 01:53:05,834
- Oh, shit!
- Oh, shit!

1564
01:53:05,960 --> 01:53:08,030
What do you mean, ''Oh, shit''?

1565
01:53:09,240 --> 01:53:10,958
All right. Hang on. Hang on.
We're goin' down.

1566
01:53:11,080 --> 01:53:12,877
Between those high tension wires?
See this wire?

1567
01:53:13,000 --> 01:53:15,355
Hey, McClane! What the fuck?

1568
01:53:17,280 --> 01:53:20,556
Hey, we got smoke! We got fuckin' smoke
and shit flyin' on me here!

1569
01:53:23,320 --> 01:53:25,197
- Truck! Truck!
- Hold on. Here we go!

1570
01:53:31,360 --> 01:53:35,399
Come on. We gotta get outta here! He's
gonna start shootin' at us any second!

1571
01:53:35,520 --> 01:53:38,398
- Get him out of here.
- Shit! The belt's stuck!
I can't get it off!

1572
01:53:38,520 --> 01:53:40,397
Look out! Here he comes!

1573
01:53:42,080 --> 01:53:43,991
Can't get out, McClane!

1574
01:53:44,120 --> 01:53:46,839
- Get him outta here.
- Where're you goin'?

1575
01:53:46,960 --> 01:53:49,076
I'm gonna try
and get his attention.

1576
01:54:06,280 --> 01:54:09,875
Oh, shit! It just keeps
gettin' better and better.

1577
01:54:15,200 --> 01:54:18,590
I had no idea Canada
could be this much fun.

1578
01:54:23,520 --> 01:54:25,988
Just give me somethin' to shoot at.
Come on, hotshot.

1579
01:54:27,080 --> 01:54:29,230
Show me that smilin' face.

1580
01:54:49,720 --> 01:54:51,551
Say hello to your brother.

1581
01:54:53,560 --> 01:54:55,152
Get outta here!

1582
01:55:10,600 --> 01:55:13,751
Yippee-ki-ay, motherfucker.

1583
01:55:16,760 --> 01:55:19,832
- Looks like you got his attention.
- Yeah. It looks like it.

1584
01:55:22,200 --> 01:55:25,476
- Think we should call a fire truck?
- Aw, fuck 'em. Let 'em cook.

1585
01:55:28,040 --> 01:55:31,077
- Oh, shit!
- What?

1586
01:55:31,200 --> 01:55:32,474
What?

1587
01:55:32,600 --> 01:55:35,672
- I left Holly hangin' on hold.
- Aw, call her back.

1588
01:55:37,080 --> 01:55:39,310
I don't know.
She's gonna be pissed.

1589
01:55:39,440 --> 01:55:41,908
She'll get over it.

1590
01:55:42,040 --> 01:55:44,998
I don't know, Zeus.

1591
01:55:45,120 --> 01:55:47,190
Like I said...

1592
01:55:47,320 --> 01:55:49,276
she's a very stubborn woman.

1593
01:55:49,400 --> 01:55:51,868
Well, she'd have to be
to stay married to you.